DESCRIPTION:Monday\, March 30\, 2026\, 1 - 3pm\n\nIf you are considering fr
	anchising as a career option\, or actively working towards a franchise agr
	eement\, this program is for you.\n\nLocation Link: Online\n\nRegistration
	 Required: Registration is required.\n\nDetailed Description: This worksho
	p is designed both for individuals at the early stage of considering franc
	hising as a career option and those actively considering a franchise but w
	ho have not yet signed the agreement.\,\n\nTopics covered include:\n\nUnde
	rstand what is and is not a franchise\, Define a positive relationship wit
	h the franchisor\, Laws and legal requirements that apply to franchising i
	n Washington State\, Important criteria in choosing a franchise\, what que
	stions to ask and how to ask them\, Research hints and tools\, A view into
	 a method to segment franchises in six different categories\, A discussion
	 on financing\, incorporation and preparation relating to a franchise awar
	d\, Navigating the myriad of franchise opportunities available\, Doing you
	r due diligence\, Narrowing down your search\, What to consider and what m
	atters to you\, Answers to your specific questions\, About the Presenter:\
	,\n\nJeff Levy\n\nis an educator\, author and coach. Herelocated from NYC 
	for a 3-person tech startup up in WA State\, has managed up to 300 people 
	across international borders and has been a franchisee since 2002. His per
	sonal experiences include raising capital\, starting and acquiring busines
	ses and investing in a franchise during a career transition. He has also s
	erved on multiple boards\, committees and has contributed voluntary work o
	n community projects.\, Registration is required. Register\n\nhere .\n\nCo
	ntact Us: If you have questions about this event\,\n\nAsk Us\n\nor call 20
	6-386-4636.\n\nADA Accommodations: We can provide accommodations for peopl
	e with disabilities at Library events. Please\n\ncontactLEAP\n\nat least s
	even days before the event to request accommodations.\, All Library progra
	ms are free and open to the public.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events
	/#/details/virtual-workshop-become-a-small-business-owner-through-franchis
	ing/18407672/2026-03-30T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
